      "content": "\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align: center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESally Ford, ABP Group Head of Health, Safety and Environment\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EAssociated British Ports (ABP), the UK\u2019s leading ports group, has today announced the appointment of Sally Ford as Group Head of Health, Safety and Environment to help further strengthen the company\u2019s focus on continuous improvement in these areas.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ESally Ford joins ABP from Southern Water, where she was Director of Health and Safety, Security and Wellbeing. She brings over 30 years of health, safety, and environmental management experience in organisations that operate critical national infrastructure, including rail, telecoms, and water sectors.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESally Ford, said:\u003C/strong\u003E \u201CI am a big believer that history is one of our greatest teachers and it is fascinating to see how, as is the case with many industrial businesses, the focus on health, safety and wellbeing has really shifted from seeing them as \u2018nice to haves\u2019 to \u2018non-negotiable\u2019.\u201D\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u201CI look forward to joining the talented team at ABP and building on this positive momentum by helping to embed safety, wellbeing and a commitment to protecting the environment into everything we do.\u201D\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EReflecting on Sally\u2019s appointment, \u003Cstrong\u003EPaul Bristowe, ABP Chief of Staff, said:\u003C/strong\u003E \u201CSally joins us at an important time as we look to further strengthen our focus on health, safety and the environment. We look forward to giving her a warm welcome to ABP and working together to achieve this goal.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u201CBeing a good neighbour to the communities surrounding our ports as well as a leading employer is very important to us. It is only with a firm commitment to both of these areas that we can deliver our twin missions of Keeping Britain Trading and Enabling the Energy Transition in a way that creates lasting value, both economic and social, for the UK.\u201D\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ESally will take up her new role on 13 October 2025, reporting to Paul Bristowe, ABP Chief of Staff.\u003C/p\u003E"
    }
